.TH TRACEROUTE 8
.SH NAME
traceroute \- print the route packets take to a network host
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B traceroute
[
.B \-m
.I max_ttl
]
.I host
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B traceroute
uses the ktcp netconf protocol to send ICMP ECHO_REQUEST packets with
incrementally increasing TTL values, tracing the path of routers between the
local system and a destination host.  Intermediate routers that decrement the
TTL to zero respond with ICMP TIME_EXCEEDED messages, revealing each hop.
The ktcp daemon must be running.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-m
.I max_ttl
Set the maximum number of hops (TTL) to probe.  The default is 30.
.SH OUTPUT
For each hop, three probes are not sent separately; a single probe is sent at
each TTL value.  A hop that responds is printed with its IP address and
round-trip time in milliseconds.  A hop that does not respond within 5 seconds
is printed as "* * *".
.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
.B traceroute 8.8.8.8
traceroute to 8.8.8.8 (8.8.8.8), 30 hops max, 12 byte packets
 1  10.0.2.2  2.345 ms
 2  * * *
 3  8.8.8.8  30.123 ms
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR ping (8),
.BR ifconfig (8),
.BR ktcp (8).
